1
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:37,850
This pole is so long.

2
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:38,960
What is it for?

3
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:39,600
It was my master

4
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,260
who made me bring it back from Kang Zixin's yard.

5
00:00:56,160 --> 00:00:56,960
Zheng Ming,

6
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,520
take this thing back to the station.

7
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:03,520
That's not appropriate, 26588.

8
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,849
What's inappropriate?

9
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:06,600
I mean the pole.

10
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,450
Oh, the pole.

11
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,240
Okay.

12
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:11,570
Your eyes are just for decoration.

13
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:13,330
They blink, but they don't see.

14
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,560
You brat.

15
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,400
Captain Zheng, you were really dumb back then.

16
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,840
You had eyes,

17
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,039
but you couldn't see.

18
00:01:25,039 --> 00:01:26,200
I'll kick your ass.

19
00:01:28,039 --> 00:01:29,200
My dad was right.

20
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:30,560
He really couldn't see.

21
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,490
You guys can see?

22
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:33,800
Then take a look.

23
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,000
See what you can find.

24
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,240
Let me tell you,

25
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:37,800
when this pole arrived,

26
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:38,600
there were no fingerprints,

27
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:39,360
no blood.

28
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,160
We didn't know what it was for.

29
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:43,050
But my master told me to keep it,

30
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,039
so I've kept it until now.

31
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,479
If my dad said to keep it,

32
00:01:47,479 --> 00:01:49,200
there must be a reason.

33
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,250
Something was carved here, right?

34
00:01:55,039 --> 00:01:56,900
It was already worn out back then,

35
00:01:57,039 --> 00:01:58,320
so we couldn't make it out.

36
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:59,360
We investigated many manufacturers

37
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,680
of this kind of pole.

38
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,840
But their poles

39
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,440
didn't have serial numbers.

40
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,680
And they said

41
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,940
they were widely used.

42
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,370
So the trail went cold here.

43
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,169
If there were no factory marks,

44
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,400
then it's very likely that

45
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:14,200
the user of this pole carved it.

46
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,200
This looks like a six-digit number.

47
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,090
The first three digits are 990.

48
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:22,480
The fourth digit

49
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,360
should be 3 or 8.

50
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:25,690
The fifth digit is 2.

51
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:27,320
The sixth digit is complicated.

52
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:28,360
It could be 0,

53
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,400
or maybe 6 or 9.

54
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,920
This way, we can potentially

55
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,800
get six sets of numbers.

56
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,240
What do these numbers mean?

57
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,700
Is it someone's birthday?

58
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,360
Look at this pole.

59
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,200
It has great elasticity and toughness.

60
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,640
Right.

61
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:56,880
Look again.

62
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:59,160
One end is worn,

63
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:00,690
but the other end is intact.

64
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:02,360
So we can see

65
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,720
that it's very likely

66
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,560
a vaulting pole.

67
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,780
But the pole isn't the murder weapon.

68
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,840
We can't follow this lead.

69
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:10,960
Captain Zheng,

70
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:13,200
regarding the suspect profiling back then...

71
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:13,640
Yes.

72
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,360
After the DNA results came out,

73
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,240
we had a new line of investigation.

74
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,079
The result showed that

75
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:20,320
the suspect's sperm

76
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,530
had no tails.

77
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,600
Not necessarily.

78
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,520
Tailless sperm could indicate sexual dysfunction,

79
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,120
but it could also come from

80
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,120
a minor who hasn't fully developed.

81
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:30,920
It's just that the information you had back then

82
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:32,450
couldn't be that specific.

83
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,920
A minor?

84
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,040
Look here.

85
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,600
This pole,

86
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,640
compared to a standard vaulting pole,

87
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,960
is nearly a meter shorter.

88
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,760
So the user of this pole...

89
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,280
It is very likely

90
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,079
a minor who practices pole vaulting.

91
00:03:45,079 --> 00:03:46,040
And they should be

92
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,320
under 15 years old.

93
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,800
Under 15?

94
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,240
Could it be a sports school student

95
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,770
practicing pole vaulting?

96
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,530
If it is a sports school,

97
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,840
then this six-digit number, 226739,

98
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,800
could possibly be,

99
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,040
just like our police badge numbers,

100
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,440
their student ID number.

101
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,880
And each student ID

102
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:05,160
corresponds to only one person.

103
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,640
This gives us a direction for the investigation.

104
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,800
We need to focus on investigating

105
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,860
those sports schools from back then.

106
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,960
Especially, we need to screen

107
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:14,400
people with this six-digit student ID.

108
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,360
Find the student corresponding to it,

109
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:17,000
then

110
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,720
extract their DNA

111
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,240
and run a comparison.

112
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,500
Hello, Principal.

113
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,320
We're from the Criminal Investigation Brigade.

114
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,320
We came today

115
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,520
to ask you some questions.

116
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,640
Okay, go ahead.

117
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,780
Please take a look.

118
00:04:32,159 --> 00:04:34,290
This pole seems to be for the high jump.

119
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,090
Do you have poles like this?

120
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:37,760
I think we do.

121
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,090
But that was many years ago.

122
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:42,040
When the school was short on funds,

123
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:42,720
we used something similar.

124
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:44,050
It was this kind of pole.

125
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,080
Principal,

126
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,400
at the bottom of this pole,

127
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:50,400
there is a number starting with 990.

128
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,920
Do you know what it means?

129
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,450
Oh, that.

130
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,800
It's a student's exam number.

131
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,720
To prevent it from getting lost,

132
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,180
we carved it onto the pole.

133
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,120
Each number

134
00:04:57,120 --> 00:04:58,580
corresponds to a student.

135
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:02,000
Do you still have the records for those students?

136
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,600
Especially those with numbers starting with 990?

137
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,200
Yes, we do.

138
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,800
We have them archived and sealed.

139
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,440
Let me find the teacher in charge back then.

140
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,520
He knows better than I do.

141
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,450
Okay, thank you.

142
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:16,240
The police stations near the dump site of the Huang Hankun case

143
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,520
didn't receive any missing report for this motorcycle.

144
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,800
I think the motorcycle used in the crime

145
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,260
must be the suspect's own.

146
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,460
It had a fake plate.

147
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:25,120
Four kilometers away from the crime scene,

148
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,380
surveillance lost track of the vehicle.

149
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,850
It matches all six sets of numbers we calculated.

150
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,240
Hello, Mr. Wu.

151
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:36,640
These six students,

152
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,640
do you remember them?

153
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:38,770
I remember them all,

154
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,000
but one didn't show up for the exam.

155
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:42,640
Which one?

156
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:46,880
Well,

157
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,120
Why didn't he take the exam back then?

158
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,240
I'm not sure about that,

159
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,960
but I remember that child very well.

160
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,000
He was from my village.

161
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,560
I saw the kid had talent,

162
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,760
and I felt sorry for him,

163
00:05:58,760 --> 00:05:59,880
so I gave him a pole.

164
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,780
I even asked the principal...

165
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,720
Look what this is.

166
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:05,720
Uncle.

167
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:06,840
This is...

168
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:07,800
for you.

169
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,860
Practice hard.

170
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:10,640
I made an exception to get you an exam number.

171
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,240
Come to our school for the test then.

172
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,500
This pole is yours now.

173
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,400
Sir,

174
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:16,200
I'm not your student.

175
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:16,730
Besides,

176
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:18,440
this is too expensive.

177
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,200
Take it.

178
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,040
Not now,

179
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,400
but how do you know you won't be?

180
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,760
Go back and practice hard.

181
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:24,360
Just focus on that highest point.

182
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,320
As long as you can clear it

183
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,250
and land safely,

184
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:27,560
you'll definitely pass.

185
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,880
I believe you can do it.

186
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,520
Thank you.

187
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:33,680
But when the exam came,

188
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,360
I don't know why he didn't show up,

189
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,400
so his exam number was voided.

190
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,000
Have you seen him since then?

191
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,440
No, I haven't.

192
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,320
Do you know anything about his family?

193
00:06:41,320 --> 00:06:43,650
I went to work in the city after graduation

194
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,880
and rarely went back to the village.

195
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,480
So I don't know the details.

196
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:48,700
Principal.

197
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
We need to take all files from 990320

198
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,080
to 990829

199
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,760
back for investigation.

200
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:54,960
Okay.

201
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:55,840
Thank you.

202
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:02,680
Hello.

203
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,440
Is this Zhang Zhitong?

204
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,280
We're from the Public Security Bureau.

205
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,280
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

206
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,780
Captain Zheng.

207
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,180
I've looked into Wen Xian's file.

208
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,840
His father was a drug addict.

209
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,080
In 1998,

210
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:31,440
he was killed by Wen Xian's mother, Xu Jinghe.

211
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:33,080
Xu Jinghe is still serving her sentence.

212
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:35,520
Wen Xian was raised by his uncle.

213
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,240
But in 2007,

214
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,900
his uncle died in an accident.

215
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:40,800
Jin Jin,

216
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,560
good work.

217
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,000
You went through over 500 documents

218
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,000
so quickly.

219
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,920
The time Wen Xian missed the exam

220
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,720
and the time of the Kang Zixin case

221
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,580
are very close.

222
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,600
Since October 2007,

223
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,840
Wen Xian seemed to vanish into thin air,

224
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,640
leaving no trace behind.

225
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,880
We heard from Wen Xian's former PE teacher

226
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:02,680
that when he was at school,

227
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,880
he lived in a guesthouse.

228
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,880
Could he have had a connection with Kang Zixin as well?

229
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:07,930
Alright.

230
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:08,880
Chen Yishi,

231
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:10,240
you and Gao

232
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,080
go to this guesthouse and ask around.

233
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:13,440
See if, after all these years,

234
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:14,400
the owner still remembers

235
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,260
either of them.

236
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,520
Captain Zheng,

237
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:27,580
come here a moment.

238
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:33,480
The motorcycle used to dump the body has appeared again.

239
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,400
This is road surveillance footage from ten minutes ago.

240
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,059
The vehicle appeared at the entrance of 101 Bar.

241
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,640
On the night of October 13,

242
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,320
this person also came to this bar.

243
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:44,049
He wasn't riding the bike then.

244
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,680
This is the footage from October 13.

245
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:47,240
Look.

246
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,970
He didn't show his face.

247
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,330
I'll ask the Tech Department to restore it later.

248
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,650
Where did you say

249
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:59,320
this person is?

250
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,240
101 Bar.

251
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,410
Are you okay?

252
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,000
I thought...

253
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,690
I thought you were dead.

254
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,040
Almost.

255
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,800
You're awake.

256
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:58,760
Where is this?

257
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:01,880
You wouldn't know even if I told you.

258
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:02,880
Anyway,

259
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,600
this isn't the continent you know.

260
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,600
Bringing a dying man like me

261
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:09,780
all the way here

262
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:11,440
must have cost a fortune.

263
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,880
Don't fish for information.

264
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,120
What's wrong?

265
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,880
You stopped talking?

266
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,250
The higher-ups are either dead

267
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,520
or captured.

268
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,920
With a small fry like you,

269
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,120
what is there to say?

270
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,560
Getting you back

271
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,440
took a lot of effort.

272
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,120
But it was worth it.

273
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,560
Tell me,

274
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,820
is the equation

275
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,200
with Dai Yu?

276
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,010
Take a guess.

277
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,880
Do I need to guess?

278
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,880
Besides him,

279
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,600
who else could you give it to?

280
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,170
But if it's with him,

281
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,050
it'll be easy to handle.

282
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,320
If you're really capable,

283
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,600
get it back from him.

284
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,000
We'll see.

285
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:20,400
After Pang Beiyuan died,

286
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:21,680
I managed to escape.

287
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,210
It's good that you're back.

288
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:25,800
By the way.

289
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,250
The glove you left me back then,

290
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,000
I can return it to you now.

291
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:36,450
It's been eleven years.

292
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,450
I finally understand your intention.

293
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,440
Zheng Ming and I went to Minghua.

294
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,050
We went to that Sichuan restaurant

295
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,280
and met the owner named Yao En.

296
00:11:47,680 --> 00:11:49,280
Chief Fu told me everything.

297
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:52,880
Yao En was the only person I trusted in Minghua.

298
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,380
I didn't keep the formula on me back then.

299
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:57,980
I gave it to him.

300
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:01,880
I told him

301
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,120
the formula

302
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:07,290
could only be given to the person wearing this glove.

303
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,330
We actually deduced that already.

304
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,660
But we were a step too late.

305
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,120
The Organization

306
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,520
made a duplicate of the glove.

307
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,330
They got there before us

308
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,200
and took the formula.

309
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,780
I didn't expect the Organization

310
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,800
to find Yao En.

311
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,640
And they even replicated

312
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,800
identical gloves

313
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,400
to steal the formula.

314
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,080
By the way,

315
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,410
there's one more thing.

316
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,400
To lure me out back then,

317
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,730
Pang Beiyuan stole my dad's ashes.

318
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,120
But recently,

319
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:51,120
someone left his ashes at my door.

320
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:52,520
What?

321
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,320
They also left this card.

322
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,680
The symbol on this card

323
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,260
is the same as the tattoo on Pang Beiyuan.

324
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,040
I think

325
00:13:01,040 --> 00:13:03,440
people from the organization are right around me,

326
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,920
monitoring my every move.

327
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:06,320
Otherwise,

328
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,680
they couldn't have

329
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,480
swapped the formula just before

330
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:11,920
Zheng Ming and I got there.

331
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,250
You and Zheng Ming must be careful.

332
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,450
Even though they got what they wanted,

333
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,560
there's no guarantee

334
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,020
they won't come after you.

335
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,320
After all, your hands

336
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,580
are so special.

337
00:13:24,920 --> 00:13:27,050
We're at the police station every day.

338
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,940
They wouldn't dare try anything.

339
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,570
On the contrary,

340
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,800
you're the one who needs to be more careful.

341
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,240
Also,

342
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,370
when do you plan to return to the force?

343
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:48,240
Being alive

344
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,240
is lucky enough.

345
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,440
To the organization,

346
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,940
now that they have what they want,

347
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,080
I'm no longer important.

348
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,280
Whatever you decide,

349
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,120
I'll support you.

350
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,240
Also,

351
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,840
I will definitely get the formula back.

352
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,000
I won't let you down.

353
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:15,440
It seems I chose the right person back then.

354
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:18,500
You're already a qualified police officer.

355
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:39,040
Keep the gloves.

356
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,000
Consider it as

357
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,650
me still being with you.

358
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:50,920
Take care.

359
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,200
Fire!

360
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,440
Fire!

361
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,900
It's been 11 years.

362
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,840
Eleven years.

363
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,040
Haishan.

364
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:37,840
Is that really you?

365
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:42,200
I have to see you.

366
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:43,400
I have to.

367
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:50,210
Who did you just see?

368
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,480
Team Leader Yan and Director Fu

369
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:54,010
ordered me to take you back.

370
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,050
Let's go.

371
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:55,800
Who was it?

372
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:57,900
Captain Zheng.

373
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,490
This is an order.

374
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:02,810
Let's go.

375
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,010
Was the person you just saw Xu Haishan?

376
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,680
Tell me.

377
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,380
Was it Xu Haishan you just met?

378
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:51,100
I won't ask why you kept it from me.

379
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:52,920
And I won't ask

380
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,650
why you wouldn't let me see him.

381
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,120
Right now,

382
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:05,250
knowing my brother is alive

383
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,280
is enough.
